Japanese Sold Net 225.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-03-09T23:59:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/japanese-sold-net-225-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 4 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in Tokyo.  Japanese investors sold 225.2 billion yen ($2.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 6.4 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 29 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 247.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 481 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 163.6 billion yen in stocks, and sold 538.9 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 105.7
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  